\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces End-to-end comparison on the mixed-fingerprint workload (16 cards, 5 seeds, mean values; bold = best in column). STPS consistently improves cluster-wide load balance, posting the lowest across-card CV and LIF and the highest JFI in every cell. This balance is achieved alongside significant congestion relief: STPS is the only scheduler that wins on both congestion ratio and mean queueing wait in every arrival mode, cutting the congestion ratio by 7--11\,\% and queue wait by 8--18\,\% relative to the best baseline, with a throughput cost under 0.3\,\%.}}{5}{table.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:q0_main}{{1}{5}{End-to-end comparison on the mixed-fingerprint workload (16 cards, 5 seeds, mean values; bold = best in column). STPS consistently improves cluster-wide load balance, posting the lowest across-card CV and LIF and the highest JFI in every cell. This balance is achieved alongside significant congestion relief: STPS is the only scheduler that wins on both congestion ratio and mean queueing wait in every arrival mode, cutting the congestion ratio by 7--11\,\% and queue wait by 8--18\,\% relative to the best baseline, with a throughput cost under 0.3\,\%}{table.1}{}}
